The paper deals with Voronoi diagrams, which are a fundamental concept in computational geometry and have applications in various fields such as computer graphics, robotics, and geographic information systems. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper includes illustrations and examples, which could indicate that it falls under cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
